  "$schema_version": "1",
  "$description": "Language-agnostic conformance vectors for Transcodely webhook verification. Every SDK that implements constructEvent must pass each vector. Producers: language-agnostic inputs (secret, body, ts, tolerance, now). Consumers: derive the signature header at runtime as `t=<ts>,v1=<HMAC-SHA-256(secret, <ts>.<body>)>` unless `signature_header` is provided literally (used to seed signature_error vectors). Note: `request.id` is `null` (not omitted) for events emitted outside a request scope — worker-callback events (e.g. `job.succeeded`) and `SendTestWebhook` deliveries. See `ok_null_request_id` / `payload_error_empty_request_id` below; `request.id: \"\"` is invalid and must be rejected, only `null` or a non-empty string (by convention `req_`-prefixed) are accepted. Keep these two vectors' bodies byte-identical with transcodely-python's local copy (see python PR #10).",
